The paper presents a new model for graph-structured data using neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The model involves a diffusion-convolution operation, which suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the model, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SI).
